## Data Sources & Architecture

### Where does all data come from?

#### Player Data (bio, stats, quiz)
- **Source:** 100% hardcoded in `constants/players.ts` вАФ compiled into the app bundle.
- **No API calls.** No network requests for player data.
- Fields per player: `name`, `displayName`, `team`, `league`, `position`, `jerseyNumber`,
  `birthDate`, `birthPlace`, `height`, `weight`, `nationality`, `formerTeams`, `funFact`,
  `teamColor`, `teamColorSecondary`, `isFeatured`, `isPopular`, `directImageUrl`, `quizQuestions[]`.
- **Quiz questions:** Also hardcoded in `players.ts`. Each player has 4 questions,
  each with 4 answer options and a `correctIndex`. Shuffled on every view in `wallpaper/[id].tsx`.
- **Total players:** 112+ across 6 leagues.
- **Adding/editing players:** Edit `constants/players.ts` directly. Redeploy app to users.

#### Player Images
- **Source:** `directImageUrl` field on each Player вАФ a hardcoded CDN URL.
- **CDN:** `r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/...` (TheSportsDB R2 storage, free).
- **No API key required.** Direct HTTPS URL to pre-fetched cutout PNG.
- **No dynamic lookup.** URLs were manually copied from TheSportsDB and baked into `players.ts`.
- **Israeli players (Beitar, Maccabi, etc.):** Most have no `directImageUrl` вАФ show gradient fallback.
- **When is the image fetched?** On first render of the image component (`expo-image`).
  `expo-image` caches downloaded images on-device automatically.
- **After first load:** Served from `expo-image` disk cache вАФ no network request.
- **Hook:** `hooks/usePlayerImages.ts` вАФ pure `useMemo`, zero network calls, zero useEffect.
  Just maps `player.directImageUrl` to the `PlayerImageData` structure. If URL is empty вЖТ `null`.

#### Team Badges (Onboarding Screen)
- **Source:** Hardcoded `BADGE_MAP` in `app/onboarding.tsx`.
- **CDN:** `crests.football-data.org/{id}.svg` (football-data.org, free SVG crests, no API key).
- **Loaded by:** `expo-image` on first render of the onboarding team grid.
- **Cached by:** `expo-image` disk cache after first load.
- **Israeli teams:** No entry in `BADGE_MAP` вЖТ render gradient circle with Hebrew initials (no network).

#### Game State / Progress
- **Source:** `AsyncStorage` key `@football_stars_game`.
- **Format:** Single JSON blob (see Data Model section below).
- **Load:** Once on app start inside `useGameState` hook (`useEffect` вЖТ `AsyncStorage.getItem`).
- **Save:** Synchronously on every state mutation via `save()` callback (`AsyncStorage.setItem`).
- **No server sync.** Progress is local-only. Uninstalling the app = data lost.
- **Version migration:** `appDataVersion` mismatch вЖТ reset state to DEFAULT_STATE вЖТ force onboarding.

#### AI Image Generation
- **Source:** Live API call to `https://pollinations.ai/p/{prompt}?width=1024&height=1792&model=flux`
- **Trigger:** User taps "„¶„Х„® „™„Ю„Х„†„™ AI" in `/(tabs)/generate`.
- **No caching.** Each generation is a fresh HTTP request. New seed = new image.
- **No API key.** Pollinations AI is free/open.
- **Result:** URL returned, rendered in `<Image>`. Not persisted unless user downloads.

#### Image Download / Share / Wallpaper
- **Flow:** `services/imageService.ts` downloads image URL вЖТ `expo-file-system` saves to device cache вЖТ
  `expo-media-library` creates asset in photo library (for download/wallpaper) or
  `expo-sharing` shares the file (for share).
- **Wallpaper on iOS/Android:** Save to gallery; user sets it manually from Photos. No native wallpaper API.

### Summary Table

| Data | Source | Network? | Cached? | On every open? |
|------|--------|----------|---------|----------------|
| Player bio / quiz | `constants/players.ts` (bundle) | вЭМ Never | N/A (bundle) | вЭМ No |
| Player images | `r2.thesportsdb.com` CDN | вЬЕ First load | вЬЕ expo-image disk cache | вЭМ After first load |
| Team badges | `crests.football-data.org` SVG | вЬЕ First load | вЬЕ expo-image disk cache | вЭМ After first load |
| Game progress | `AsyncStorage` local | вЭМ Never | N/A (local) | вЬЕ Yes (fast, sync) |
| AI generation | `pollinations.ai` live API | вЬЕ Every time | вЭМ No | Only on demand |

